lead_paragraph: Reggie Jackson scored 22 points, Tobias Harris added 21 and the Detroit Pistons overcame Jimmy Butler's first career triple-double to beat the Chicago Bulls 94-90 on Saturday night.

headline.print_headline: Jackson, Harris Lift Pistons Over Bulls 94-90
